1 Regresie liniarÄƒ simplÄƒ

1.1 Metoada celor mai mici pÄƒtrate

ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ estimatorii \(\hat{\beta}_0\) È™i \(\hat{\beta}_1\) obÈ›inuÈ›i prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate, adicÄƒ valorile coeficienÈ›ilor \(\beta_0\) È™i \(\beta_1\) care minimizeazÄƒ funcÈ›ia

\[ S(\beta_0, \beta_1) = \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \beta_0 - \beta_1 x_i)^2 \]

sunt daÈ›i de expresiile

\[ \hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x \quad \text{È™i} \quad \hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \]

Trebuie sÄƒ determinÄƒm

\[ (\hat{\beta}_0, \hat{\beta}_1) = \underset{(\beta_0,\beta_1)\in\mathbb{R}\times\mathbb{R}}{\arg\min} S(\beta_0, \beta_1) \]

È™i observÃ¢nd cÄƒ funcÈ›ia \(S(\beta_0, \beta_1)\) este convexÄƒ ea admite un punct de minim. Acesta se obÈ›ine ca soluÈ›ie a sistemului \(\nabla S = 0\) de ecuaÈ›i normale,

\[ \left\{\begin{array}{ll} \frac{\partial S}{\partial \beta_0} = -2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \beta_0 - \beta_1 x_i) = 0\\ \frac{\partial S}{\partial \beta_1} = -2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i(y_i - \beta_0 - \beta_1 x_i) = 0 \end{array}\right. \]

Din prima ecuaÈ›ie obÈ›inem prin sumare \(n\beta_0 + \beta_1\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i = \sum_{i=1}^{n}y_i\) ceea ce conduce la \(\hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x\).

A doua ecuaÈ›ie conduce la

\[ \beta_0\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i + \beta_1\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i^2 = \sum_{i=1}^{n}x_iy_i \]

È™i Ã®nlocuind \(\beta_0\) cu expresia obÈ›inutÄƒ anterior, obÈ›inem soluÈ›ia

\[ \hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i(x_i - \bar x)} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \]

De asemenea, se poate verifica cÄƒ \(S(\beta_0, \beta_1)\) se scrie sub forma

\[\begin{align*} S(\beta_0, \beta_1) &= n\left[\beta_0 - (\bar y - \beta_1\bar x)\right]^2 + \left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\right]\left[\beta_1 - \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right]^2 \\ &\quad + \left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2\right]\left[1 - \frac{\left(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)\right)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}\right] \end{align*}\]

care justificÄƒ Ã®n egalÄƒ mÄƒsurÄƒ soluÈ›ia obÈ›inutÄƒ anterior.

ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ estimatorii obÈ›inuÈ›i prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate, \(\hat\beta_0\) È™i \(\hat\beta_1\), sunt estimatori nedeplasaÈ›i.

CoeficienÈ›ii \(\hat\beta_0\) È™i \(\hat\beta_1\) obÈ›inuÈ›i prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate sunt daÈ›i de \(\hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x\) È™i \(\hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\) (aceÈ™tia sunt variabile aleatoare deoarece sunt funcÈ›ii de \(Y_i\) care sunt variabile aleatoare). Ãnlocuind Ã®n expresia lui \(\hat\beta_1\) pe \(y_i\) cu \(\beta_0+\beta_1 x_i + \varepsilon_i\) avem

\[\begin{align*} \hat\beta_1 &= \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)y_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(\beta_0+\beta_1 x_i + \varepsilon_i)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\\ &= \frac{\beta_0\overbrace{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)}^{ = 0} + \beta_1 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)x_i + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} = \frac{\beta_1 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2 + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\\ &= \beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \end{align*}\]

Conform ipotezei modelului de regresie liniarÄƒ simplÄƒ, \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_i] = 0\), prin urmare \(\mathbb{E}[\hat\beta_1] = \beta_1\) ceea ce aratÄƒ cÄƒ \(\hat\beta_1\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\beta_1\).

Ãn mod similar,

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat\beta_0] = \mathbb{E}[\bar y] - \bar x\mathbb{E}[\hat\beta_1] = \beta_0 + \bar x\beta_1 - \bar x\beta_1 = \beta_0 \] ceea ce aratÄƒ cÄƒ \(\hat\beta_0\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\beta_0\).

CalculaÈ›i matricea de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ a estimatorilor \(\hat\beta_0\) È™i \(\hat\beta_1\).

NotÄƒm cu \(W = \begin{pmatrix}Var(\hat \beta_0) & Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1)\\ Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1) & Var(\hat \beta_1)\end{pmatrix}\) matricea de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ a estimatorilor \(\hat\beta_0\) È™i \(\hat\beta_1\).

Avem, folosind expresia lui \(\hat\beta_1\) determinatÄƒ la punctul anterior È™i homoscedasticitatea È™i necorelarea erorilor \(Cov(\varepsilon_i, \varepsilon_j) = \delta_{ij}\sigma^2\), cÄƒ

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat \beta_1) &= Var\left(\beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right) = Var\left(\frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right)\\ &= \frac{Var\left(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i\right)}{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\right]^2} = \frac{\sum_{i,j}(x_i - \bar x)(x_j - \bar x)Cov(\varepsilon_i, \varepsilon_j)}{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\right]^2}\\ &= \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\sigma^2}{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\right]^2} = \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \end{align*}\]

Din expresia \(Var(\hat \beta_1)\) observÄƒm cÄƒ dacÄƒ \(\sigma^2\) este micÄƒ (cu alte cuvinte \(y_i\) sunt aproape de dreapta de regresie) atunci estimarea este mai precisÄƒ. De asemenea, se constatÄƒ cÄƒ pe mÄƒsurÄƒ ce valorile \(x_i\) sunt mai dispersate Ã®n jurul valorii medii \(\bar x\) estimarea coeficientului \(\hat \beta_1\) este mai precisÄƒ (\(Var(\hat \beta_1)\) este mai micÄƒ). Acest fenomen se poate observa È™i Ã®n figura de mai jos Ã®n care am generat \(100\) de valori aleatoare \(X\) È™i \(100\) de valori pentru \(Y\) dupÄƒ modelul

\[ y = 1 + 2 x + \varepsilon \] cu \(\varepsilon\sim \mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2)\). Dreapta roÈ™ie descrie adevÄƒrata relaÈ›ie \(f(x) = 1 + 2x\) Ã®n populaÈ›ie iar dreapta albastrÄƒ reprezintÄƒ dreapta de regresie calculatÄƒ cu ajutorul metodei celor mai mici pÄƒtrate (OLS). Dreptele albastru deschis au fost generate tot cu ajutorul metodei celor mai mici pÄƒtrate atunci cÃ¢nd variem \(\sigma^2\) (Ã®n figura din stÃ¢nga) È™i respectiv pe \(x_i\) Ã®n jurul lui \(\bar x\) (Ã®n figura din dreapta).

Pentru a determina \(Var(\hat \beta_0)\), vom folosi relaÈ›ia \(\hat \beta_0 = \bar y - \hat \beta_1 \bar x\) ceea ce conduce la

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat \beta_0) &= Var(\bar y - \hat \beta_1 \bar x) = Var(\bar y) - 2Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1 \bar x) + Var(\hat \beta_1 \bar x)\\ &= Var\left(\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}y_i\right) - 2\bar x Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1) + \bar x^2 Var(\hat \beta_1)\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2}{n} + \bar x^2 \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} - 2\bar x Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1). \end{align*}\]

Pentru \(Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1)\) avem (È›inÃ¢nd cont de faptul cÄƒ \(\beta_0\), \(\beta_1\) È™i \(x_i\) sunt constante)

\[\begin{align*} Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1) &= Cov\left(\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}y_i, \beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\varepsilon_j}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2} \right) = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}Cov\left(\beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i + \varepsilon_i, \beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\varepsilon_j}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\right)\\ &= \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}Cov\left(\varepsilon_i, \frac{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\varepsilon_j}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\right) = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\frac{1}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}Cov\left(\varepsilon_i, \sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\varepsilon_j\right)\\ &= \frac{1}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\frac{1}{n}\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)Cov(\varepsilon_i, \varepsilon_i=j) = \frac{1}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\frac{1}{n}\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\delta_{ij}\sigma^2\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\frac{1}{n}\underbrace{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)}_{=0} = 0 \end{align*}\]

prin urmare

\[ Var(\hat \beta_0) = \frac{\sigma^2}{n} + \bar x^2 \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} = \frac{\sigma^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2}{n\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \]

Calculul covarianÈ›ei dintre \(\hat \beta_0\) È™i \(\hat \beta_1\) rezultÄƒ aplicÃ¢nd relaÈ›iile de mai sus

\[ Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1) = Cov(\bar y - \hat \beta_1\bar x, \hat \beta_1) = Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1) - \bar x Var(\hat \beta_1) = -\frac{\sigma^2 \bar x}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \]

ObservÄƒm cÄƒ \(Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1)\leq 0\) iar intuitiv, cum dreapta de regresie (bazatÄƒ pe estimatorii obÈ›inuÈ›i prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate) \(\bar y = \hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 \bar x\) trece prin centrul de greutate al datelor \((\bar x, \bar y)\), dacÄƒ presupunem \(\bar x > 0\) remarcÄƒm cÄƒ atunci cÃ¢nd creÈ™tem panta (creÈ™tem \(\hat\beta_1\)) ordonata la origine scade (scade \(\hat\beta_0\)) È™i reciproc.

Matricea de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ a estimatorilor \(\hat\beta_0\) È™i \(\hat\beta_1\) devine

\[ W = \begin{pmatrix}Var(\hat \beta_0) & Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1)\\ Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1) & Var(\hat \beta_1)\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}\frac{\sigma^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2}{n\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} & -\frac{\sigma^2 \bar x}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\\ -\frac{\sigma^2 \bar x}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} & \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\end{pmatrix}. \]

ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ Ã®n cadrul modelului de regresie liniarÄƒ simplÄƒ, suma valorilor reziduale este nulÄƒ.

ObservÄƒm, folosind definiÈ›ia \(\hat\varepsilon_i = y_i - \hat y_i\), cÄƒ

\[\begin{align*} \sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \hat y_i) = \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \hat \beta_0 - x_i\hat\beta_1)\\ &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}\left[y_i - \underbrace{(\bar y - \bar x\hat\beta_1)}_{= \hat \beta_0} - x_i\hat\beta_1\right] = \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y) -\hat\beta_1 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x) = 0 \end{align*}\]

ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ Ã®n modelul de regresie liniarÄƒ simplÄƒ statistica \(\hat\sigma^2 = \frac{1}{n-2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i^2\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\sigma^2\).

ÈšinÃ¢nd cont de faptul cÄƒ \(\hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x\) È™i \(\bar y = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \bar x + \bar \varepsilon\) (prin Ã®nsumarea dupÄƒ \(i\) a relaÈ›iilor \(y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i +\varepsilon_i\)) gÄƒsim cÄƒ

\[\begin{align*} \hat\varepsilon_i &= y_i - \hat y_i = (\beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i +\varepsilon_i) - (\hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_i) \\ &= (\underbrace{\bar y - \beta_1 \bar x - \bar \varepsilon}_{=\beta_0} + \beta_1 x_i +\varepsilon_i) - (\bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x + \hat\beta_1 x_i)\\ &= (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)(x_i - \bar x) + (\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon) \end{align*}\]

È™i prin dezvoltarea binomului È™i utilizÃ¢nd relaÈ›ia \(\hat\beta_1 = \beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\) gÄƒsim

\[\begin{align*} \sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i^2 &= (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x) + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2 + 2(\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)\\ &= (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x) + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2 + 2(\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i - 2(\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)\bar\varepsilon\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\\ &= (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x) + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2 - 2(\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\\ &=\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2 - (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2. \end{align*}\]

LuÃ¢nd media gÄƒsim cÄƒ

\[ \mathbb{E}\left(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i^2\right) = \mathbb{E}\left(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2\right) - \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2 Var(\hat\beta_1) = (n-1)\sigma^2 - \sigma^2 = (n-1)\sigma^2 \]

unde am folosit cÄƒ \(\mathbb{E}\left(\frac{1}{n-1}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2\right) = \sigma^2\) (deoarece \(Var(\varepsilon_i) = \sigma^2\)).

ConcluzionÄƒm cÄƒ \(\hat\sigma^2 = \frac{1}{n-2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i^2\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\sigma^2\).

Fie \(x_{n+1}\) o nouÄƒ valoare pentru variabila \(X\) È™i ne propunem sÄƒ prezicem valoarea \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului

\[ y_{n+1} = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{n+1} + \varepsilon_{n+1} \]

cu \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\), \(Var(\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\) È™i \(Cov(\varepsilon_{n+1}, \varepsilon_i)=0\) pentru \(i = 1,\ldots,n\).

ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ varianÈ›a rÄƒspunsului mediu prezis este

\[ Var(\hat y_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[\frac{1}{n} + \frac{(x_{n+1} - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right] \]

\[ Var(\hat\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[1 + \frac{1}{n} + \frac{(x_{n+1} - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right]. \]

Cum \(\hat y_{n+1} = \hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_{n+1}\) avem

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat y_{n+1}) &= Var(\hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_{n+1}) = Var(\hat\beta_0) + 2Cov(\hat\beta_0, \hat\beta_1) + x_{n+1}^2Var(\hat\beta_1)\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2}{n\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} - 2\frac{\sigma^2 \bar x}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} + \frac{\sigma^2x_{n+1}^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\left[\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2 - 2x_{n+1}\bar x + x_{n+1}^2\right]\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\left[\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i -\bar x)^2 + \bar x^2 - 2x_{n+1}\bar x + x_{n+1}^2\right]\\ &= \sigma^2\left[\frac{1}{n} + \frac{(x_{n+1} - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right]. \end{align*}\]

ConstatÄƒm cÄƒ atunci cÃ¢nd \(x_{n+1}\) este departe de valoarea medie \(\bar x\) rÄƒspunsul mediu are o variabilitate mai mare.

Pentru a obÈ›ine varianÈ›a erorii de predicÈ›ie \(\hat\varepsilon_{n+1} = y_{n+1} - \hat y_{n+1}\) sÄƒ observÄƒm cÄƒ \(y_{n+1}\) depinde doar de \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\) pe cÃ¢nd \(\hat y_{n+1}\) depinde de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(i\in\{1,2,\ldots,n\}\). Din necorelarea erorilor deducem cÄƒ

\[ Var(\hat\varepsilon_{n+1}) = Var(y_{n+1} - \hat y_{n+1}) = Var(y_{n+1}) + Var(\hat y_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[1 + \frac{1}{n} + \frac{(x_{n+1} - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right]. \]

1.2 Coeficientul de determinare \(R^2\) È™i coeficientul de corelaÈ›ie

Ãn aceastÄƒ secÈ›iune Ã®ncercÄƒm sÄƒ abordÄƒm problema de regresie liniarÄƒ simplÄƒ Ã®ntr-un context geometric. Din punct de vedere vectorial dispunem de doi vectori: vectorul \(X = (x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_n)^\intercal\) a celor \(n\) observaÈ›ii ale variabilei explicative È™i vectorul \(Y = (y_1, y_2, \ldots, y_n)^\intercal\) compus din cele \(n\) observaÈ›ii ale variabilei rÄƒspuns, pe care vrem sÄƒ o explicÄƒm. Cei doi vectori aparÈ›in spaÈ›iului \(\mathbb{R}^n\).

Fie \(\mathbf{1} = (1,1,\ldots,1)^\intercal\in\mathbb{R}^n\) È™i \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) subspaÈ›iul liniar din \(\mathbb{R}^n\) de dimensiune \(2\) generat de vectorii \(\{\mathbf{1}, X\}\) (aceÈ™ti vectori nu sunt coliniari deoarece \(X\) conÈ›ine cel puÈ›in douÄƒ elemente distincte). NotÄƒm cu \(\hat Y\) proiecÈ›ia ortogonalÄƒ a lui \(Y\) pe subspaÈ›iul \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) È™i cum \(\{\mathbf{1}, X\}\) formeazÄƒ o bazÄƒ Ã®n \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) deducem cÄƒ existÄƒ \(\hat\beta_0, \hat\beta_1\in \mathbb{R}\) astfel ca \(\hat Y = \hat\beta_0\mathbf{1} + \hat\beta_1 X\). Cum, din definiÈ›ia priecÈ›iei ortogonale, \(\hat Y\) este unicul vector din \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) care minimizeazÄƒ distanÈ›a euclidianÄƒ (deci È™i pÄƒtratul ei)

\[ \left\lVert Y - \hat Y \right\rVert = \sum_{i = 1}^{n}[y_i - (\hat\beta_0 + \hat \beta_1 x_i)]^2 \]

deducem cÄƒ \(\hat\beta_0, \hat\beta_1\) coincid cu valorile obÈ›inute prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate. Astfel coeficienÈ›ii \(\hat\beta_0\) È™i \(\hat\beta_1\) se reprezintÄƒ coordonatele proiecÈ›iei ortogonale a lui \(Y\) pe subspaÈ›iul generat de vectorii \(\{\mathbf{1}, X\}\) (a se vedea figura de mai jos).

ObservÄƒm cÄƒ, Ã®n general, vectorii \(\{\mathbf{1}, X\}\) nu formeazÄƒ o bazÄƒ ortogonalÄƒ Ã®n \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) (cu excepÈ›ia cazului Ã®n care \(\langle \mathbf{1}, X\rangle = n\bar x = 0\)) prin urmare \(\hat\beta_0\mathbf{1}\) nu este proiecÈ›ia ortogonalÄƒ a lui \(Y\) pe \(\mathbf{1}\) (aceasta este \(\frac{\langle Y, \mathbf{1}\rangle}{\lVert \mathbf{1}\rVert^2}\mathbf{1} = \bar y\mathbf{1}\)) iar \(\hat\beta_1 X\) nu este proiecÈ›ia ortogonalÄƒ a lui \(Y\) pe \(X\) (aceasta fiind \(\frac{\langle Y, X\rangle}{\lVert X\rVert^2}X\)).

Fie \(\hat\varepsilon = Y - \hat Y = (\hat\varepsilon_1, \hat\varepsilon_2, \ldots, \hat\varepsilon_n)^\intercal\) vectorul valorilor reziduale. AplicÃ¢nd Teorema lui Pitagora (Ã®n triunghiul albastru) rezultÄƒ (descompunerea ANOVA pentru regresie) cÄƒ

\[\begin{align*} \left\lVert Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2 &= \left\lVert \hat Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2 + \left\lVert \underbrace{\hat\varepsilon}_{Y - \hat Y}\right\rVert^2\\ \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2 &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar y)^2 + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\underbrace{\hat\varepsilon_i}_{y_i - \hat y_i})^2\\ SS_T &= SS_{reg} + RSS \end{align*}\]

Din definiÈ›ia coeficientului de determinare \(R^2\) avem cÄƒ

\[ R^2 = \frac{SS_{reg}}{SS_T} = \frac{\left\lVert \hat Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2}{\left\lVert Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{\left\lVert \hat \varepsilon\right\rVert^2}{\left\lVert Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2} \]

È™i conform figurii de mai sus \(R^2 = \cos^2(\theta)\). Prin urmare dacÄƒ \(R^2 = 1\), atunci \(\theta = 0\) È™i \(Y\in\mathcal{M}(X)\), deci \(y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i\), \(i\in\{1,2,\ldots,n\}\) (punctele eÈ™antionului sunt perfect aliniate) iar dacÄƒ \(R^2 = 0\), deducem cÄƒ \(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar y)^2 = 0\), deci \(\hat y_i = \bar y\) (modelul liniar nu este adaptat Ã®n acest caz, nu putem explica mai bine decÃ¢t media).

ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ

\[ R^2 = r_{xy}^2 = r_{y\hat y}^2 \]

unde \(r_{xy}\) este coeficientul de corelaÈ›ie empiric dintre \(x\) È™i \(y\).

Din definiÈ›ia coeficientului de determinare È™i folosind coeficienÈ›ii \(\hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x\) È™i \(\hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\) obÈ›inuÈ›i prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate avem

\[\begin{align*} R^2 &= \frac{\left\lVert \hat Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2}{\left\lVert Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_i - \bar y)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x + \hat\beta_1\bar x - \bar y)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}\\ &= \frac{\hat\beta_1^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} = \left(\frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right)^2\frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}\\ & = \frac{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)\right]^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} = r_{xy}^2. \end{align*}\]

Pentru a verifica a doua parte, \(R^2 = r_{y\hat y}^2\), sÄƒ observÄƒm cÄƒ

\[ r_{y\hat y}^2 = \frac{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{\hat y})(y_i - \bar y)\right]^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{\hat y})^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} \]

\[ r_{y\hat y}^2 = \frac{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \bar y)\right]^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}. \]

De asemenea

\[\begin{align*} \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \bar y) &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \hat y_i + \hat y_i - \bar y) \\ &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \hat y_i) + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})^2 \end{align*}\]

È™i cum

\[\begin{align*} \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \hat y_i) &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat \beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \hat \beta_0 - \hat\beta_1 x_i) \\ &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x + \hat\beta_1 x_i - \bar{y})[(y_i - \bar y ) - \hat\beta_1 (x_i - \bar x)]\\ &= \hat\beta_1 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y) - \hat\beta_1^2 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2 \\ &= \underbrace{\frac{S_{xy}}{S_{xx}}}_{\hat\beta_1}S_{xy} - \frac{S_{xy}^2}{S_{xx}^2}S_{xx} = 0 \end{align*}\]

deducem cÄƒ \(r_{y\hat y}^2 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} = R^2\).

2 Regresie liniarÄƒ multiplÄƒ

Principiul problemei de regresie este de a modela o variabilÄƒ \(y\), numitÄƒ variabilÄƒ rÄƒspuns sau variabilÄƒ dependentÄƒ (cea pe care vrem sÄƒ o explicÄƒm), cu ajutorul unei funcÈ›ii care depinde de un anumit numÄƒr de variabile \(\boldsymbol x = (x_1,\ldots, x_p)^\intercal\), numite variabile explicative sau predictori sau independente (vom folosi Ã®n general primele douÄƒ denumiri)

2.2 Metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate

ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ dacÄƒ ipoteza \(\mathcal{H}_1\) este adevÄƒratÄƒ atunci estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) obÈ›inut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate este

Ne propunem sÄƒ prezentÄƒm mai multe metode de calcul pentru estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\).

  1. Metoda geometricÄƒ

Din punct de vedere geometric, ne plasÄƒm Ã®n spaÈ›iul variabilelor \(\mathbb{R}^n\) (am presupus cÄƒ \(n>p\))). Vectorul variabilelor rÄƒspuns \(\boldsymbol Y\in \mathbb{R}^n\) iar matricea de design \(\boldsymbol{X}\) poate fi vÄƒzutÄƒ ca fiind formatÄƒ din \(p+1\) vectori coloanÄƒ, \(\boldsymbol{X} = \left[\underbrace{\boldsymbol X_0}_{\mathbf{1} = (1,\cdots,1)}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right]\).

Ãncepem prin a reaminti cÃ¢teva noÈ›iuni de algebrÄƒ liniarÄƒ, pentru mai multe detalii se poate consulta monografia (Ornea and Turtoi 2000). Fiind datÄƒ matricea (de design) \(\boldsymbol{X}\in\mathcal{M}_{n,p+1}(\mathbb{R})\) putem defini nucleul matricei

Se poate arÄƒta (a se vedea (Ornea and Turtoi 2000, Capitolul 1)) cÄƒ \(\dim \ker(\boldsymbol{X}) = p + 1 - \mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol{X})\) È™i cÄƒ \(\dim \mathrm{Im}(\boldsymbol{X}) = \mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol{X})\) ceea ce conduce la \(\dim \ker(\boldsymbol{X}) + \dim \mathrm{Im}(\boldsymbol{X}) = p+1\) (caz particular al teoremei lui Grassman).

Ãn particular pentru \(\boldsymbol T = \boldsymbol Z\) avem matricea de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ \(Var(\boldsymbol Z) = Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol Z)\) care, Ã®n conformitate cu relaÈ›ia de mai sus, este egalÄƒ cu

Un calcul direct aratÄƒ cÄƒ dacÄƒ \(\boldsymbol A\in\mathcal{M}_{l,m}(\mathbb{R})\) È™i \(\boldsymbol B\in\mathcal{M}_{q, k}(\mathbb{R})\) sunt douÄƒ matrice cu coeficienÈ›i constanÈ›i atunci

\[ Cov\left(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol B\boldsymbol T\right) = \boldsymbol A Cov\left(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol T\right)\boldsymbol B^\intercal \]

iar atunci cÃ¢nd \(\boldsymbol T = \boldsymbol Z\) È™i \(\boldsymbol A = \boldsymbol B\) gÄƒsim cÄƒ \(Var(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Z) = \boldsymbol A Var(\boldsymbol Z)\boldsymbol A^\intercal\). De asemenea, dacÄƒ \(\boldsymbol Z\), \(\boldsymbol T\), \(\boldsymbol U\) È™i \(\boldsymbol V\) sunt vectori aleatori de dimensiune \(m\times 1\) iar \(a,b,c,d\in\mathbb{R}\) sunt constante reale atunci

\[ Cov(a\boldsymbol Z + b\boldsymbol T, c\boldsymbol U + d\boldsymbol V) = ac Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol U) + ad Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol V) + bc Cov(\boldsymbol T, \boldsymbol U) + bd Cov(\boldsymbol T, \boldsymbol V) \]

È™i respectiv

\[ Var(a\boldsymbol Z + b\boldsymbol T) = a^2 Var(\boldsymbol Z) + ab\left(Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol T) + Cov(\boldsymbol T, \boldsymbol Z)\right) + b^2 Var(\boldsymbol T). \]

Pentru a verifica nedeplasarea estimatorului \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) obÈ›inut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate sÄƒ notÄƒm cÄƒ, Ã®n contextul ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_1\), acesta este \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\). Astfel putem scrie

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \mathbb{E}\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\right] = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y] = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon] \]

È™i cum \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon] = 0\) conform \(\mathcal{H}_2\) deducem cÄƒ

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X}_{ = I_{p+1}}\boldsymbol \beta + \underbrace{\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon]}_{=0} = \boldsymbol \beta. \]

Pentru matricea de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ avem

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) &= Var\left((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\right) = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right) \left((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal\right)^\intercal \\ &= (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right) \boldsymbol X (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \end{align*}\]

unde Ã®n ultima egalitate am È›inut cont de simetria matricei \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\): \(\left((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right)^\intercal = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\). Din modelul de regresie avem cÄƒ \(Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right) = Var\left(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon\right) = Var(\boldsymbol\varepsilon)\) È™i din ipoteza \(\mathcal{H}_2\) avem \(Var(\boldsymbol\varepsilon) = \sigma^2 I_n\) prin urmare

\[ Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \underbrace{Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right)}_{= \sigma^2 I_n} \boldsymbol X (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \sigma^2 \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X}_{= I_{p+1}} (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}. \]

Estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) obÈ›inut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate este estimatorul liniar, nedeplasat de varianÈ›Äƒ minimalÄƒ (BLUE).

Rezultatul acestui exerciÈ›iu este cunoscut È™i sub denumirea de Teorema Gauss-Markov (a se vedea (Faraway 2015, Capitolul 2)). Pentru a putea soluÈ›iona acest exerciÈ›iu trebuie pentru Ã®nceput sÄƒ remarcÄƒm cÃ¢teva aspecte: Ã®n primul rÃ¢nd, liniaritatea estimatorului se referÄƒ la liniaritatea Ã®n raport cu \(\boldsymbol Y\), adicÄƒ vorbim de clasa estimatorilor de forma \(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y\) unde \(\boldsymbol A\in\mathcal{M}_{p+1, n}(\mathbb{R]})\); Ã®n al doilea rÃ¢nd pentru a determina varianÈ›a minimalÄƒ avem nevoie de o relaÈ›ie parÈ›ialÄƒ de ordine pe mulÈ›imea matricelor simetrice, ori o asemenea relaÈ›ie existÄƒ È™i spune cÄƒ \(\boldsymbol S_1\leq \boldsymbol S_2\) atunci cÃ¢nd \(\boldsymbol S = \boldsymbol S_2 - \boldsymbol S_1\) este pozitiv definitÄƒ (valorile proprii ale lui \(\boldsymbol S\) sunt \(\geq 0\)), cu alte cuvinte \(\boldsymbol S_1\leq \boldsymbol S_2\) dacÄƒ \(\boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol S_1\boldsymbol x\leq \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol S_2\boldsymbol x\) pentru orice \(\boldsymbol x\).

Ãn acest context, cum \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un estimator nedeplasat (conform exerciÈ›iului anterior) È™i liniar deoarece \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{A} \boldsymbol Y\), considerÃ¢nd \(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}\) un alt estimator liniar È™i nedeplasat pentru \(\boldsymbol \beta\) vrem sÄƒ arÄƒtÄƒm cÄƒ \(Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta})\geq Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta})\). Avem, conform proprietÄƒÈ›ilor matricei de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ de mai sus, descompunerea

\[ Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}) = Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} + \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) + Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) + Cov(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}, \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) + Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}, \tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}). \]

Cum matricele de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ sunt pozitiv semidefinite (pentru \(\boldsymbol a\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\) avem \(\boldsymbol a^\intercal Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta})\boldsymbol a = Var(\boldsymbol a^\intercal\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta})\geq 0\), deoarece varianÈ›a este pozitivÄƒ) este suficient sÄƒ arÄƒtÄƒm cÄƒ \(Cov(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}, \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = 0\). Liniaritatea estimatorului \(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}\) implicÄƒ \(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} = \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y\) iar nedeplasarea acestuia, \(\mathbb{E}[\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \boldsymbol \beta\) pentru orice \(\boldsymbol \beta\), conduce la \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y] = \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta = \boldsymbol \beta\) pentru orice \(\boldsymbol \beta\) de unde \(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol X = I_{p+1}\).

Ãn final avem

\[\begin{align*} Cov(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}, \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) &= Cov(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}, \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) - Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = Cov\left(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y, (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\right) - Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta})\\ &= \boldsymbol A Cov\left(\boldsymbol Y, \boldsymbol Y\right) \left((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal\right)^\intercal - Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = \boldsymbol A \underbrace{Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right)}_{=\sigma^2 I_n}\boldsymbol X (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} - \underbrace{Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta})}_{=\sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}}\\ &= \sigma^2\underbrace{\boldsymbol A \boldsymbol X}_{= I_{p+1}} (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} - \sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = 0. \end{align*}\]

Fie \(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon} = \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) vectorul valorilor reziduale. ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) È™i \(\mathcal{H}_2\) au loc relaÈ›iile

  1. \(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}] = 0\) È™i \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}\)
  2. \(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol Y}] = \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta\) È™i \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}) = \sigma^2 P_{X}\)
  3. \(Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \hat{\boldsymbol Y}) = 0\)
  1. Am vÄƒzut cÄƒ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = P_X\boldsymbol Y\) prin urmare

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon} = (\hat{\varepsilon}_1,\ldots, \hat{\varepsilon}_n)^\intercal = \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y} = (I - P_X)\boldsymbol Y = P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y = P_{X^\perp}(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon) = P_{X^\perp} \boldsymbol\varepsilon \]

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}] = \mathbb{E}[P_{X^\perp} \boldsymbol\varepsilon] = P_{X^\perp} \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol\varepsilon] = 0 \] iar, È›inÃ¢nd seama de proprietatea de simetrie \(P_{X^\perp}^\intercal = P_{X^\perp}\) È™i idempotenÈ›Äƒ \(P_{X^\perp}^2 = P_{X^\perp}\) a matricei de proiecÈ›ie,

\[ Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = Var(P_{X^\perp} \boldsymbol\varepsilon) = P_{X^\perp} Var(\boldsymbol\varepsilon) P_{X^\perp}^\intercal = P_{X^\perp} \underbrace{Var(\boldsymbol\varepsilon)}_{=\sigma^2 I_n} P_{X^\perp} = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}^2 = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}. \]

  1. Din nedeplasarea lui \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) È™i definiÈ›ia lui \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) avem

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol Y}] = \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \boldsymbol X\mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta. \]

Ãn mod similar

\[ Var(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}) = Var(\boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = \boldsymbol X \underbrace{Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta})}_{=\sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}}\boldsymbol X^\intercal = \sigma^2\underbrace{\boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{=P_X} = \sigma^2 P_X. \]

  1. Pentru a calcula \(Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \hat{\boldsymbol Y})\) folosim \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}\) È™i \(Var(\boldsymbol Y) = Var(\boldsymbol \varepsilon) = \sigma^2 I_n\) È™i avem
\[\begin{align*} Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \hat{\boldsymbol Y}) &= Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \boldsymbol Y) - Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = Cov(P_{X^\perp} \boldsymbol Y, \boldsymbol Y) - \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp} \\ &= P_{X^\perp}Var(\boldsymbol Y) P_{X^\perp}^\intercal - \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp} = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp} - \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp} = 0. \end{align*}\]

Statistica \(\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\sigma^2\).

Ca sÄƒ arÄƒtÄƒm cÄƒ \(\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\sigma^2\) trebuie sÄƒ calculÄƒm \(\mathbb{E}\left[\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right]\). \[ \mathbb{E}\left[\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right] = \mathbb{E}\left[\mathrm{Tr}\left(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right)\right] = \mathbb{E}\left[\mathrm{Tr}\left(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\right)\right] \]

\[ \mathbb{E}\left[\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right] = \sigma^2 \left[n - (p+1)\right] \]

Folosind estimatorul \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) pentru \(\sigma^2\) putem construi un estimator \(\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}}^2\) pentru varianÈ›a \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}) = \sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\):

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}}^2 = \hat{\sigma}^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}. \]

Ãn particular, un estimator pentru abaterea standard a estimatorului coeficientului \(\beta_j\), \(\hat{\beta}_j\), este dat de elementul \(j+1\) de pe diagonala matricii \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\):

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_j} = \hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}},\quad j = 0,1,\ldots,p. \]

Fie \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) o nouÄƒ observaÈ›ie È™i considerÄƒm \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\). Ne propunem sÄƒ prezicem valoarea \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului

Fie modelul de regresie \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) unde matricea de design se scrie

\[ \boldsymbol {X}=\begin{pmatrix} 1 & x_{11} & \cdots & x_{1p}\\ \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots\\ 1 & x_{n1} & \cdots & x_{np} \end{pmatrix}_{n\times(p+1)} = \left[\underbrace{\boldsymbol X_0}_{\mathbf{1} = (1,\cdots,1)}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right] = \left[\mathbf{1}|\boldsymbol Z\right] \]

Reamintim, e.g. (Henderson and Searle 1981), cÄƒ dacÄƒ \(\boldsymbol F\) este o matrice pÄƒtratÄƒ inversabilÄƒ care se scrie sub formÄƒ de bloc de patru submatrice

Ãn cazul problemei noastre avem \(\boldsymbol A = 1\), \(\boldsymbol B = \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\), \(\boldsymbol C = \bar{\boldsymbol x}\) È™i \(\boldsymbol D = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\boldsymbol Z\) prin urmare

\[ Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right). \]

ÈšinÃ¢nd cont de scrierea sub formÄƒ de blocuri a matricei \(\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\right)^{-1}\) gÄƒsim cÄƒ

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1} &= \begin{pmatrix}1 & \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal\end{pmatrix} \frac{1}{n}\begin{pmatrix}1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & -\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\\ -\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix}1\\ \boldsymbol z_{n+1}\end{pmatrix} \\ &= \frac{1}{n}\left(1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} - \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} - \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1} + \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1}\right). \end{align*}\]

NotÃ¢nd cu \(\boldsymbol Z_c\) matricea (centratÄƒ) cu coloanele \(\boldsymbol X_j - \bar{\boldsymbol x}_j\mathbf{1}\), \(j = 1,\ldots,p\) putem observa cÄƒ

\[ \boldsymbol \Gamma = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\boldsymbol Z - \bar{\boldsymbol x}\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z_c^\intercal\boldsymbol Z_c \]

AceastÄƒ ultimÄƒ relaÈ›ie ne spune cÄƒ prima coloanÄƒ a lui \(\boldsymbol X\) se scrie ca o combinaÈ›ie liniarÄƒ de celelalte, ceea ce Ã®nseamnÄƒ cÄƒ \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X)\leq p\) de unde concluzionÄƒm cÄƒ matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) nu este inversabilÄƒ.

Cum \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este simetricÄƒ È™i pozitiv definitÄƒ deducem cÄƒ \((\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\geq 0\), cu egalitate dacÄƒ È™i numai dacÄƒ \(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} = \bar{\boldsymbol x}\), adicÄƒ \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal) = (1, \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal)\). Ãn acest caz \(Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1+\frac{1}{n}\right)\), rezultat care generalizeazÄƒ rezultatul corespunzÄƒtor de la regresia liniarÄƒ simplÄƒ: trebuie sÄƒ ne plasÄƒm Ã®n centrul norului de puncte ale variabilelor explicative pentru a prezice variabila rÄƒspuns cu mai multÄƒ precizie.

2.4 Modelul (condiÈ›ionat) normal

ConsiderÄƒm modelul de regresie liniarÄƒ

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon \]

\[ l(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = \log L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = -\frac{n}{2}\log{2\pi\sigma^2} -\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2. \]

Vrem sÄƒ determinÄƒm

\[ (\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}, \hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2) = \underset{(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2)\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\times(0,\infty)}{\arg\max} l(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) \]

È™i observÄƒm cÄƒ pentru \(\sigma^2\) fixat, a maximiza funcÈ›ia \(l(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)\) revine la a determina valoarea lui \(\boldsymbol\beta\) care minimizeazÄƒ \(\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2\), aceasta ne fiind alta decÃ¢t \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) obÈ›inut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate. Astfel gÄƒsim cÄƒ

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM} = \hat{\boldsymbol\beta} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol Y. \]

Pentru a determina \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2\) sÄƒ observÄƒm cÄƒ problema revine la a determina soluÈ›ia ecuaÈ›iei

\[ \frac{\partial l(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)}{\partial \sigma^2} = -\frac{n}{2\sigma^2} + \frac{1}{2\sigma^4}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}\rVert^2 = 0 \]

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2 = \frac{n - (p+1)}{n}\hat{\sigma}^2, \]

deci estimatorul de verosimilitate maximÄƒ \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2\) a lui \(\sigma^2\) est un estimator deplasat. Ãn cele ce urmeazÄƒ vom considera estimatorul nedeplasat \(\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i}{n - (p+1)}\) ca estimator al lui \(\sigma^2\).

2.4.1 RepartiÈ›iile estimatorilor, intervale È™i regiuni de Ã®ncredere

Ãnainte de a investiga repartiÈ›iile estimatorilor \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) È™i \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) pentru modelul de regresie liniarÄƒ sub ipoteza de normalitate, sÄƒ reamintim cÃ¢teva noÈ›iuni legate de vectorii gaussieni (pentru mai multe detalii se poate consulta (Seber and Lee 2003, Capitolul 2) sau (Jacod and Protter 2003, Capitolul 16)).

Spunem cÄƒ un vector \(\boldsymbol Y = (Y_1,\ldots,Y_n)\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este un vector gaussian dacÄƒ toate combinaÈ›iile liniare \(\sum_{i=1}^{n}a_iY_i\) sunt repartizate normal (posibil degenerat dacÄƒ toÈ›i coeficienÈ›ii sunt nuli). \[ f_{\boldsymbol Y}(\boldsymbol y) = \frac{1}{(2\pi)^{\frac{n}{2}}\sqrt{\det{\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}}}} e^{-\frac{1}{2}(\boldsymbol y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol y - \boldsymbol \mu)} \]

Ãn cazul Ã®n care matricea \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) nu este inversabilÄƒ Ã®nseamnÄƒ cÄƒ \(\boldsymbol Y\) ia valori Ã®ntr-un subspaÈ›iu de dimensiune \(n_0<n\) unde este repartizat ca un vector gaussian de dimensiune \(n_0\).

Figura de mai jos prezintÄƒ patru repartiÈ›ii normale bivariate (\(n=2\)) \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y})\), cu \(\boldsymbol\mu = (\mu_1, \mu_2)^\intercal\) iar \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \begin{pmatrix}\sigma_{11} & \sigma_{12}\\ \sigma_{21} & \sigma_{22}\end{pmatrix}= \begin{pmatrix}\sigma_{1}^2 & \sigma_{12}\\ \sigma_{12} & \sigma_{2}^2\end{pmatrix}\), rotite cu unghiul \(\alpha\). Ãn acest caz densitatea de repartiÈ›ie este

\[ f_{\boldsymbol Y}(y_1,y_2) = \frac{1}{2\pi\sigma_1\sigma_2\sqrt{1-\rho^2}}e^{-\frac{1}{2(1-\rho^2)}\left[\left(\frac{y_1 - \mu_1}{\sigma_1}\right)^2 - 2\rho\left(\frac{y_1 - \mu_1}{\sigma_1}\right)\left(\frac{y_2 - \mu_2}{\sigma_2}\right) + \left(\frac{y_2 - \mu_2}{\sigma_2}\right)^2\right]} \]

Una dintre proprietÄƒÈ›ile importante ale vectorilor gaussieni este stabilitatea prin transformÄƒri afine: dacÄƒ \(\boldsymbol A\in\mathcal{M}_{m,n}(\mathbb{R})\) È™i \(\boldsymbol b\in\mathcal{M}_{m,1}(\mathbb{R})\) sunt respectiv o matrice È™i un vector de scalari atunci

\[ \boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}) \Longrightarrow \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y + \boldsymbol b \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol\mu + \boldsymbol b, \boldsymbol A\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\boldsymbol A^\intercal) \]

De asemenea, plecÃ¢nd de la funcÈ›ia caracteristicÄƒ, se poate verifica proprietatea de independenÈ›Äƒ a componentelor unui vector gaussian care ne spune cÄƒ acestea sunt independente dacÄƒ È™i numai dacÄƒ matricea de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ este o matrice diagonalÄƒ.

Avem urmÄƒtorul rezultat care face legÄƒtura dintre repartiÈ›ia normalÄƒ È™i repartiÈ›ia \(\chi^2\):

\[ (\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) \sim \chi_n^2 \]

\[ \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta \boldsymbol Q^\intercal \Longrightarrow \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1} = \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-1} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal = \left(\boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-\frac{1}{2}} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal\right)\left(\boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-\frac{1}{2}} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal\right) = \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}. \]

\[ (\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) = \left(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\right)^\intercal\left(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\right) \]

È™i cum vectorii gaussieni rÄƒmÃ¢n gaussieni È™i prin aplicarea unor transformÄƒri afine (vezi rezultatul de mai sus) avem cÄƒ

\[ \boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}) \Longrightarrow \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) \sim\mathcal{N}(0, I_n). \]

Astfel vectorul \(\boldsymbol V = [\boldsymbol V_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol V_n]^\intercal = \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\), care nu este altceva decÃ¢t vectorul \(\boldsymbol Y\) centrat È™i redus, este gaussian standard (\(\boldsymbol V_j\sim\mathcal{N}(0,1)\) È™i \(\boldsymbol V_i\) È™i \(\boldsymbol V_j\) sunt independente) È™i

  1. Rezultatele din exerciÈ›iile anterioare conduc la urmÄƒtoarele intervale (atunci cÃ¢nd parametrii sunt consideraÈ›i separat) È™i regiuni de Ã®ncredere (atunci cÃ¢nd luÄƒm Ã®n calcul mai mulÈ›i parametrii simultan prin urmare È›inem cont È™i de dependenÈ›a dintre ei) pentru parametrii modelului de regresie liniarÄƒ:

  1. Un interval de Ã®ncredere bilateral de nivel de Ã®ncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(\sigma^2\) este dat de

\[ I_{\sigma^2} = \left[\frac{[n - (p+1)]\hat{\sigma}^2}{\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)}, \frac{[n - (p+1)]\hat{\sigma}^2}{\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)}\right] \]

unde \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\) È™i \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\) sunt cuantilele de ordin \(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\) È™i respectiv \(\frac{\alpha}{2}\) a repartiÈ›iei \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\).

  1. O regiune de Ã®ncredere de nivel de Ã®ncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(q\) (\(q\leq p+1\)) parametrii \(\beta_j\), notaÈ›i \((\beta_{j_1},\ldots,\beta_{j_q})\), este datÄƒ de
  • atunci cÃ¢nd \(\sigma\) este cunoscutÄƒ, de

\[ RC^{1-\alpha}(R\boldsymbol \beta) = \left\{R\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^q\,|\, \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) \leq \chi^2_q(1-\alpha)\right\} \]

\[ RC^{1-\alpha}(R\boldsymbol \beta) = \left\{R\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^q\,|\, \frac{1}{q\hat{\sigma}^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) \leq F_{q, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \]

unde \(R\) este o matrice de dimensiune \(q\times(p+1)\) cu toate elementele nule exceptÃ¢nd elementele \(R_{i,j_i}\) care sunt egale cu \(1\).

Ca ilustrare a regiunii de Ã®ncredere de mai sus, sÄƒ presupunem cÄƒ \(p\geq 2\) È™i \(q = 2\) iar matricea \(R\) este

\[ R = \begin{pmatrix}1 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0\\ 0 & 1 & 0 & \cdots & 0\end{pmatrix} \]

ceea ce conduce la \(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) = \begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0\\ \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix}\). DacÄƒ presupunem cÄƒ \(\sigma^2\) este necunoscut atunci regiunea de Ã®ncredere pentru \((\beta_0,\beta_1)\) este datÄƒ de

\[ \small RC^{1-\alpha}(\beta_0,\beta_1) = \left\{(\beta_0,\beta_1)\in\mathbb{R}^2\,|\, \frac{1}{2\hat{\sigma}^2}\begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0 & \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix}\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}\begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0\\ \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix} \leq F_{2, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \normalsize \]

È™i notÃ¢nd cu \(c_{ij}\) elementul de pe linia \(i\) coloana \(j\) a matricei \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\), gÄƒsim cÄƒ

\[ \scriptsize RC^{1-\alpha}(\beta_0,\beta_1) = \left\{(\beta_0,\beta_1)\in\mathbb{R}^2\,|\,\frac{c_{22}(\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0)^2 - 2c_{12}(\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0)(\hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1) + c_{11}(\hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1)^2}{2\hat{\sigma}^2(c_{11}c_{22} - c_{12}^2)}\leq F_{2, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \normalsize \]

ceea ce aratÄƒ cÄƒ regiunea are formÄƒ de elipsÄƒ (vezi (Ornea and Turtoi 2000, Capitolul 2, SecÈ›iunea 16)).

Fie \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) o nouÄƒ observaÈ›ie È™i considerÄƒm \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\). Ne propunem sÄƒ prezicem valoarea \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului

\[ y_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol \beta + \varepsilon_{n+1} \]

cu \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma^2)\) independentÄƒ de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(1\leq i\leq n\).

ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ un interval de Ã®ncredere de nivel de Ã®ncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(y_{n+1}\) este dat de

\[ \scriptsize \left[\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} - t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}, \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} + t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}\right] \normalsize \]

PlecÃ¢nd de la un eÈ™antion de talie \(n\), \((\boldsymbol x_1, y_1), \ldots, (\boldsymbol x_n, y_n)\), gÄƒsim estimatorul de verosimilitate maximÄƒ (acelaÈ™i cu cel obÈ›inut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate) \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) a lui \(\boldsymbol\beta\) cu ajutorul cÄƒruia putem prezice valoarea \(\hat{y}_{n+1}\) dupÄƒ relaÈ›ia

Pentru a cuantifica eroarea de predicÈ›ie \(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\) folosim urmÄƒtoarea descompunere

\[ y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) + \varepsilon_{n+1}, \]

care este o sumÄƒ de douÄƒ variabile gaussiene independente, \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\) È™i \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) care este un vector gaussian care depinde de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(1\leq i\leq n\). Prin urmare \(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\) este un vector gaussian È™i È›inÃ¢nd cont cÄƒ matricea de varianÈ›Äƒ-covarianÈ›Äƒ \(Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right)\) avem

\[ y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1} \sim \mathcal{N}\left(0, \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right)\right). \] AceastÄƒ relaÈ›ie se rescrie sub forma

\[ \frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\sigma\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}} \sim \mathcal{N}(0, 1) \]

È™i Ã®nlocuind \(\sigma\) cu estimatorul sÄƒu \(\hat{\sigma}\) obÈ›inem

\[ \frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}} = \frac{\frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\sigma\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}}}{\frac{\sigma}{\hat{\sigma}}} = \frac{\frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\sigma\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}}}{\sqrt{\frac{\frac{[n - (p+1)]\sigma}{\hat{\sigma}}}{n - (p+1)}}} \sim \frac{\mathcal{N}(0,1)}{\sqrt{\frac{\chi^2_{n-(p+1)}}{n - (p+1)}}}. \]

RemarcÄƒm cÄƒ numÄƒrÄƒtorul È™i numitorul sunt variabile aleatoare independente deoarece \(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) + \varepsilon_{n+1}\) este independentÄƒ de \(\hat{\sigma}\) pentru cÄƒ \(\hat{\sigma}\) este independentÄƒ de \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) È™i de \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\) (estimatorul \(\hat{\sigma}\) nu depinde decÃ¢t de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(1\leq i\leq n\)). Prin urmare gÄƒsim cÄƒ

\[ \frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}} \sim t_{n-(p+1)} \]

de unde rezultÄƒ intervalul de Ã®ncredere dorit.

2.4.2 Testare de ipoteze statistice

ConsiderÄƒm modelul de regresie liniarÄƒ

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon \]

sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\) È™i \(\mathcal{H}_2': \, \boldsymbol \varepsilon \sim\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2 I_n)\). Ãn particula, acest model ne spune cÄƒ \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y] = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathcal{M}(X)\) unde \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) este subspaÈ›iul de dimensiune \(p+1\) a lui \(\mathbb{R}^n\) generat de coloanele matricei de design \(\boldsymbol X\).

Pentru Ã®nceput, Ã®n aceastÄƒ secÈ›iune ne propunem sÄƒ testÄƒm dacÄƒ ultimii \(q\) coeficienÈ›i, \(q = p + 1 - p_0\leq p+1\), sunt nuli, altfel spus vrem sÄƒ testÄƒm ipotezele

\[ H_0:\, \beta_{p_0+1} = \cdots = \beta_p = 0 \quad \text{versus}\quad H_1:\,\exists j\in\{p_0+1,\ldots,p\}\, \beta_j\neq 0 \]

Ãn termeni de model, ipoteza \(H_0\) ne spune cÄƒ modelul revine la

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X_0\boldsymbol \beta_0 + \boldsymbol \varepsilon_0 \]

sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X_0) = p_0\) È™i \(\mathcal{H}_2': \, \boldsymbol \varepsilon_0 \sim\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2 I_n)\), unde matricea \(\boldsymbol X_0\in\mathcal{M}_{n,p_0}(\mathbb{R})\) este compusÄƒ din primele \(p_0\) coloane ale lui \(\boldsymbol X\) iar \(\boldsymbol \beta_0\in\mathcal{M}_{p_0,1}(\mathbb{R})\). Fie \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\) subspaÈ›iul lui \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) de dimensiune \(p_0\) generat de coloanele lui \(\boldsymbol X_0\) (deoarece \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\) deducem cÄƒ \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X_0) = p_0\)). Sub ipoteza \(H_0\) avem cÄƒ \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y] = \boldsymbol X_0\boldsymbol \beta_0\in\mathcal{M}(X_0)\).

Sub ipoteza \(H_0\) statistica de test

\[ F = \frac{n - (p+1)}{q}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2} = \frac{n - (p+1)}{q}\frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS} \sim F_{q, n - (p+1)} \]

unde \(F_{q, n - (p+1)}\) este repartiÈ›ia lui Fisher cu \((q, n - (p+1))\) grade de libertate.

  1. Abordarea geometricÄƒ

Vom prezenta mai jos o abordare din punct de vedere geometric a problemei de testare. ConsiderÄƒm spaÈ›iul \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\subset\mathcal{M}(X)\) È™i am vÄƒzut cÄƒ sub ipoteza nulÄƒ avem \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y] = \boldsymbol X_0\boldsymbol \beta_0\in\mathcal{M}(X_0)\). Ãn aceastÄƒ situaÈ›ie, metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate consistÄƒ Ã®n proiectarea lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\) pentru a obÈ›ine \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\) (vezi figura de mai jos).

Ideea procedurii de testare, È™i prin urmare a deciziei de a respinge sau nu ipoteza nulÄƒ, este urmÄƒtoarea: dacÄƒ proiecÈ›ia \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\) a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\) este aproape de proiecÈ›ia \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) atunci nu respingem ipoteza nulÄƒ, Ã®n caz contrar o respingem Ã®n favoarea alternativei \(H_1\). De fapt, dacÄƒ informaÈ›ia adusÄƒ de cele douÄƒ modele nu diferÄƒ foarte mult atunci este recomandat sÄƒ pÄƒstrÄƒm modelul mai simplu (principiul parcimoniei).

Pentru a cuantifica apropierea dintre cele douÄƒ proiecÈ›ii putem considera distanÈ›a euclidianÄƒ \(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2\) dintre acestea. AceastÄƒ distanÈ›Äƒ variazÄƒ Ã®n funcÈ›ie de datele È™i de unitÄƒÈ›ile de mÄƒsurÄƒ a acestora È™i pentru a evita aceastÄƒ problemÄƒ de scarÄƒ se recomandÄƒ standardizarea acestei distanÈ›e prin Ã®mpÄƒrÈ›irea ei la pÄƒtratul normei erorii reziduale \(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2 = \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 = [n - (p+1)]\hat{\sigma}^2\). Cum vectorii aleatori \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\) È™i \(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\) nu aparÈ›in Ã®n subspaÈ›ii de aceeaÈ™i dimensiune trebuie sÄƒ Ã®i Ã®mpÄƒrÈ›im È™i prin gradele de libertate corespunzÄƒtoare, respectiv \(q = p+1 - p_0\) È™i \(n - (p+1)\). ObÈ›inem astfel statistica de test

\[ F = \frac{\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{p+1-p_0}}{\frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)}} = \frac{n - (p+1)}{(p+1) - p_0}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2}. \]

Pentru a putea utiliza aceastÄƒ statisticÄƒ de test este necesar sÄƒ determinÄƒm repartiÈ›ia sa sub ipoteza nulÄƒ. NotÃ¢nd cu \(P_X\) È™i respectiv \(P_{X_0}\) matricele de proiecÈ›ie ortogonalÄƒ pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) È™i \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\), È™tim cÄƒ

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0 = P_X\boldsymbol Y - P_{X_{0}}\boldsymbol Y \]

È™i cum \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\subset \mathcal{M}(X)\), deci \(P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y = P_{X_0}P_{X}\boldsymbol Y\) È™i

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0 = P_{X}\boldsymbol Y - P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y = (I_n - P_{X_0})P_X\boldsymbol Y = P_{X_0}^\perp P_{X}\boldsymbol Y. \]

Astfel am gÄƒsit cÄƒ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\in\mathcal{M}(X_0)^\perp\cap \mathcal{M}(X)\) È™i cum \(\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\in\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) gÄƒsim cÄƒ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0 \perp \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\). Vectorii \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\) È™i \(\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) sunt elemente din spaÈ›ii ortogonale ceea ce implicÄƒ \(Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0, \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}) - 0\) È™i cum sunt È™i vectori gaussieni (conform ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_2'\)) deducem cÄƒ sunt È™i independenÈ›i ceea ce aratÄƒ cÄƒ numÄƒrÄƒtorul È™i numitorul lui \(F\) sunt independente.

Conform Teoremei lui Cochran avem pentru numitor

\[ \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X^\perp}(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon)\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol\varepsilon\rVert^2\sim\chi^2_{n - (p+1)} \]

iar pentru numÄƒrÄƒtor

\[ \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X_0}^\perp P_{X}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X_0}^\perp P_{X}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta)\rVert^2 \sim \chi^2_{q} \]

Sub \(H_0\), parametrul \(\lVert P_{X_0}^\perp P_{X}\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2\) este nul deoarece \(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\in\mathcal{M}(X_0)\) ceea ce conduce la

\[ F\overset{H_0}{\sim} F_{q, n - (p+1)}. \]

Putem observa de asemenea cÄƒ aplicÃ¢nd Teorema lui Pitagora

\[\begin{align*} \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 &= \lVert\boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y + P_X\boldsymbol Y - P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert (I_n - P_X)\boldsymbol Y + P_{X_0}P_X\boldsymbol Y - P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 \\ &= \lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y + (I_n - P_{X_0})P_X\boldsymbol Y \rVert^2 = \lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y + P_{{X_0}^\perp}P_X\boldsymbol Y \rVert^2\\ &= \lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_{{X_0}^\perp}P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 + \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 \end{align*}\]

altfel spus

\[ \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 = \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 - \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 = RSS_0 - RSS. \]

Ne propunem sÄƒ testÄƒm ipoteza nulÄƒ \(H_0:\, \beta_j = 0\) versus ipoteza alternativÄƒ \(H_1:\, \beta_j \neq 0\). PropuneÈ›i o procedurÄƒ de testare pentru cele douÄƒ ipoteze.

AceastÄƒ problemÄƒ este un caz particular al rezultatului obÈ›inut anterior pentru \(q = 1\). Avem statistica de test

\[ F = \frac{n - (p+1)}{1}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2} = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\hat{\sigma}^2} \]

cu ajutorul cÄƒreia putem construi regiunea criticÄƒ

\[ C = \{\omega\,|\,F(\omega)>F_{1, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\}. \]

Acest test este echivalent cu testul bazat pe statistica de test repartizatÄƒ student cu \(n - (p+1)\) grade de libertate (mai exact \(F^2 = T_j\))

\[ T_j = \frac{\hat{\beta}_j}{\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_j}} = \frac{\hat{\beta}_j}{\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}}. \]

Regiunea criticÄƒ a testului este

\[ C = \left\{\omega\,|\,T_j(\omega)>t_{n - (p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\right\}. \]

Aceasta este forma sub care testul de semnificativitate pentru un coeficient apare Ã®n R.

PropuneÈ›i o procedurÄƒ de testare pentru ipotezele

\[ H_0:\, \beta_1 = \ldots = \beta_p = 0 \quad \text{versus}\quad H_1:\,\exists j\in\{1,\ldots,p\}\, \beta_j\neq 0 \]

Vrem sÄƒ testÄƒm dacÄƒ variabilele explicative au sau nu influenÈ›Äƒ asupra variabilei rÄƒspuns, cu alte cuvinte vrem sÄƒ testÄƒm dacÄƒ toÈ›i coeficienÈ›ii sunt nuli exceptÃ®nd constanta (\(\beta_0\)) - acesta este testul care apare ca rezultat atunci cÃ¢nd efectuÄƒm sumarul modelului liniar Ã®n R (comanda summary(model)). Suntem Ã®n cazul particular Ã®n care \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0 = \bar{y}\mathbf{1}\) È™i obÈ›inem statistica de test a lui Fisher (testul global al lui Fisher)

\[ F = \frac{n - (p+1)}{p}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2} \sim F_{p, n - (p+1)} \] sau exprimatÄƒ Ã®n termeni de coeficient de determinare

\[ F = \frac{n - (p+1)}{p}\frac{R^2}{1 - R^2} \sim F_{p, n - (p+1)}. \]

Vrem sÄƒ testÄƒm ipotezele

\[ H_0:\, \beta_{p_0+1} = \cdots = \beta_p = 0 \quad \text{versus}\quad H_1:\,\exists j\in\{p_0+1,\ldots,p\}\, \beta_j\neq 0 \]

cu ajutorul testului bazat pe raportul de verosimilitÄƒÈ›i. ArÄƒtaÈ›i cÄƒ acest test este echivalent cu testul \(F\) al lui Fisher.

Testul bazat pe raportul de verosimilitate este

\[ \Lambda(\mathbf{y})=\frac{\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_0}L(\theta|\mathbf{y})}{\sup_{\theta\in\Theta}L(\theta|\mathbf{y})}, \]

unde \(\Theta\) este spaÈ›iul parametrilor modelului, \(\Theta_0\) este spaÈ›iul parametrilor corespunzÄƒtor ipotezei nule iar \(L(\theta|\mathbf{x})\) este funcÈ›ia de verosimilitate.

ObservÄƒm cÄƒ spaÈ›iul parametrilor modelului este

\[ \Theta = \left\{(\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2)|\,\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}, \sigma^2\in (0,\infty)\right\}, \]

cel corespunzÄƒtor ipotezei nule este

\[ \Theta_0 = \left\{(\boldsymbol \beta_0, \sigma^2)|\,\boldsymbol \beta_0\in\mathbb{R}^{p_0}, \sigma^2\in (0,\infty)\right\} \]

iar funcÈ›ia de verosimilitate este

\[ L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = \prod_{i = 1}^{n}f_{Y}(y_i) = \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}}\right)^n e^{-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \boldsymbol x_i^\intercal\boldsymbol\beta)^2} = \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}}\right)^n e^{-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2}. \]

ObservÄƒm cÄƒ

\[ \sup_{\theta\in\Theta}L(\theta|\mathbf{y}) = \sup_{\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2} L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = L(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}, \hat{\sigma}^2_{VM};\boldsymbol Y) \]

unde \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}=\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) este estimatorul obÈ›inut prin metoda celor mai mici pÄƒtrate iar \(\hat{\sigma}^2_{VM} = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}{n} = \frac{RSS}{n}\). Astfel gÄƒsim

\[ \sup_{\theta\in\Theta}L(\theta|\mathbf{y}) = \sup_{\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2} L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = \left(\frac{n}{2\pi\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}} = \left(\frac{n}{2\pi RSS}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}}. \]

Sub \(H_0\) avem

\[ sup_{\theta\in\Theta_0}L(\theta|\mathbf{y}) = \sup_{\boldsymbol\beta_0, \sigma^2\in\Theta_0} L(\boldsymbol\beta_0, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = L(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{0}, \hat{\sigma}^2_{0};\boldsymbol Y) = \left(\frac{n}{2\pi RSS_{0}}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}} \]

unde \(RSS_0 = \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X_0\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_0\rVert^2\) iar \(\hat{\sigma}^2_{0} = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X_0\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_0\rVert^2}{n} = \frac{RSS_0}{n}\).

Prin urmare raportul de verosimilitate devine

\[ \Lambda(\mathbf{y})=\frac{\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_0}L(\theta|\mathbf{y})}{\sup_{\theta\in\Theta}L(\theta|\mathbf{y})} = \frac{\left(\frac{n}{2\pi RSS_{0}}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}}}{\left(\frac{n}{2\pi RSS}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}}} = \left(\frac{RSS_0}{RSS}\right)^{-\frac{n}{2}} \]

iar regiunea criticÄƒ a testului se scrie (testul respinge ipoteza nulÄƒ atunci cÃ¢nd statistica \(\Lambda\) este suficient de micÄƒ)

\[ C = \left\{\boldsymbol Y\in\mathbb{R}^n\,|\, \Lambda(\boldsymbol Y)< \lambda_0 \right\}. \] ObservÄƒm cÄƒ pentru \(\lambda>0\), funcÈ›ia \(h(\lambda) = \lambda^{-\frac{2}{n}}-1\) este descrescÄƒtoare, adicÄƒ \(\lambda<\lambda_0\) implicÄƒ \(h(\lambda)>h(\lambda_0)\). Avem

\[ h(\lambda)>h(\lambda_0) \iff \frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS}>h(\lambda_0) \iff \frac{n - (p+1)}{(p+1) - p_0}\frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS}>f_0 \]

unde \(f_0\) se determinÄƒ din condiÈ›ia

\[ \mathbb{P}_{H_0}\left(\frac{n - (p+1)}{(p+1) - p_0}\frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS}>f_0\right) = \alpha \]

È™i cum \(\frac{n - (p+1)}{(p+1) - p_0}\frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS}\sim F_{(p+1) - p_0, n - (p+1)}\) conform exerciÈ›iului deducem cÄƒ \(f_0 = f_{(p+1) - p_0, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\). Am gÄƒsit cÄƒ regiunea criticÄƒ a testului bazat pe raportul de verosimilitate este identicÄƒ cu cea a testului \(F\) a lui Fisher (vezi exerciÈ›iul ).
